         MACRO ,
&NM      UNITSKIP ,
.*
.*  THIS MACRO IS USED BY EXHIBIT DISPLAY ROUTINES (EXHDXXXX) TO
.*  ELIMINATE (CONTROL) UNITS FROM DISPLAY CONSIDERATION
.*
.*  THE UNITS ARE DEFINED IN OPTIONS VARIABLES UNITSK AND UNITSK2
.*  EACH TWO BYTE SPECIFIED EITHER A CONTROL UNIT ADDRESS OR
.*  A CHANNEL NUMBER FOLLOWED BY X
.*
         LCLC  &I
&I       SETC  '&SYSNDX'
.*
         LM    R15,R1,SPUBXLE  GET THE BXLE VALUES
         ICM   R14,3,UCBNAME  LOAD THE UCB NAME
ZZU&I.L  CLM   R14,3,0(R15)  CONTROL UNIT MATCH ?
         BE    NEXTUCB       YES; SKIP IT
         CLI   1(R15),C'X'   CHANNEL SKIP ?
         BNE   ZZU&I.B       NO; TRY ANOTHER
         CLM   R14,2,0(R15)  CHANNEL MATCH ?
         BE    NEXTUCB       YES; SKIP IT
ZZU&I.B  BXLE  R15,R0,ZZU&I.L  TRY NEXT SPECIFICATION
         MEND  ,
